---
import '../styles/static-pages.styles.scss';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const pageTitle = "Triplay.ai Privacy Policy: Your Data\'s Safety";
const description = 'Unlock the secrets of safeguarding your data with Triplay.ai\'s Privacy Policy!  Your data fortress awaits behind one click. Explore now!';
const keywords = 'Privacy Policy, personal information, data collection, data security, communication, website improvement, service providers, legal reasons, business transfers';
const openGraph = {
	basic: {
		title: "Triplay.ai Privacy Policy: Your Data\'s Safety",
		description: 'Unlock the secrets of safeguarding your data with Triplay.ai\'s Privacy Policy!  Your data fortress awaits behind one click. Explore now!',
		type: "website",
		image: "https://triplay.ai/triplay-logo.svg",
		url: 'https://triplay.ai/privacy',
	}
};
---
<BaseLayout
	pageTitle={pageTitle}
	metaTitle={pageTitle}
	description={description}
	metaDescription={description}
	keywords={keywords}
	openGraph={openGraph}
>
	<main class='static-page'>
		<div class='container static-content__container'>
			<h1>Privacy Policy for Triplay</h1>
			<div class='static-content'>
				<p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> <span>November 27, 2023</span></p>
				<p>Welcome to Triplay
					(&quot;Triplay&quot;, &quot;Website&quot;, &quot;Service&quot;, &quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot; or &quot;our&quot;).
					We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This
					Privacy Policy outlines our commitment to protecting your privacy and provides information on how we
					collect, use, and protect your personal information.</p>
				<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
				<p>We collect the following types of information:</p>
				<section>
					<h3>1.1. Personal Identification Information</h3>
					<p>When you sign up using Google or Apple sign in, we collect your first and last names, and your email
						address. This information is necessary for setting up your account, verifying your identity, and
						communicating with you.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>1.2. Trip Preferences</h3>
					<p>We collect information about the cities you select as travel destinations, your travel intensity, and
						your interests. This information helps us to provide a personalized user experience.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>1.3. Transaction Data</h3>
					<p>When you subscribe to our paid license through Stripe, we may receive certain payment and customer
						information. Stripe&apos;s use of your personal information is governed by their Privacy Policy.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>1.4. Device and Usage Information</h3>
					<p>When you access our website, we may collect certain information automatically, such as your IP address,
						browser type, operating system, referring URLs, pages you visit, and the dates and times of your
						interactions with our website.</p>
				</section>
				<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
				<section>
					<h3>2.1. Trip Planning</h3>
					<p>We use the information you provide to design and create personalized travel itineraries and
						recommendations based on your preferences and requirements.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>2.2. Communication</h3>
					<p>We may use your contact information to communicate with you about your custom trip, provide updates,
						respond to inquiries, and deliver important Website-related information.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>2.3. Website Improvement:</h3>
					<p>The information collected helps us understand how users interact with our website, identify areas for
						improvement, and enhance user experience.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>2.4. Legal and Security Purposes</h3>
					<p>We may use your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or enforceable
						governmental requests. Additionally, we use your data to protect against security threats, fraud, and
						abuse.</p>
				</section>
				<h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
				<p>We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information only under
					the following circumstances:</p>
				<section>
					<h3>3.1. Service Providers</h3>
					<p>We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf.
						These service providers have access to your personal information only to perform these tasks and are
						obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>3.2. Legal Reasons</h3>
					<p>We may disclose your personal information if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that
						such action is necessary to comply with a legal obligation, protect and defend our rights or property, or
						protect the personal safety of users of the Website or the public.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>3.3. Business Transfers</h3>
					<p>In the event of a merger, acquisition, or any other business transaction involving our company, your
						information may be transferred along with other assets.</p>
				</section>
				<h2>4. Data Security</h2>
				<div class='card'>
					<p>We employ data collection, storage, and processing practices, and security measures to protect against
						unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of your personal information.</p>
				</div>
				<h2>5. GDPR Data Protection Rights</h2>
				<div class='card'>
					<p>Your data protection is important to us. Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have
						rights regarding your personal data:</p>
					<p> - Access: Obtain a copy of your data – know what we hold.</p>
					<p> - Rectification: Correct inaccurate data – keep your records right.</p>
					<p> - Erasure: Request data deletion – control your online presence.</p>
					<p> - Restriction: Limit data processing – decide how your data is used.</p>
					<p> - Portability: Receive data in a usable format – switch services seamlessly.</p>
					<p> - Object: Challenge data use – have a say in your data&apos;s purpose.</p>
					<p> - Automated Decisions: Avoid automated profiling – maintain human oversight.</p>
					<p> - Withdraw Consent: Change data usage preferences – control your choices.</p>
					<p>Please contact us at <a href='mailto:support@triplay.ai'>support@triplay.ai</a> for assistance, we have
						one month to respond in line with data protection laws.</p>
				</div>
				<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
				<section>
					<h3>6.1. Access and Correction</h3>
					<p>You can access your personal information by logging into your account or by contacting us directly.</p>
				</section>
				<section>
					<h3>6.2. Marketing Communications</h3>
					<p>If you no longer wish to receive marketing communications from us, you can opt-out by contacting us.</p>
				</section>
				<h2>7. Requesting Account Deletion</h2>
				<div class='card'>
					<p>If you have registered or logged in to our platform using Google or Facebook authentication and wish to
						delete your account, please follow the guidelines below. To initiate the account deletion process, send us
						an email at <a href='mailto:support@triplay.ai'>support@triplay.ai</a> with the subject line &quot;Request
						for Account Deletion.&quot; In the body of the email, kindly provide any pertinent details that would help
						us verify your identity. Once we receive your request, our team will process it and you will receive a
						confirmation email once the deletion is complete. Please note that deleting your account with us will
						remove all your custom itineraries and preferences from our platform but will not delete or modify your
						Google or Facebook account in any way. If you encounter any issues or have further questions regarding
						account deletion, please feel free to reach out. Your privacy and data security are our utmost priorities.
					</p>
				</div>
				<h2>8. Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2>
				<div class='card'>
					<p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new
						Privacy Policy on this page and updating the &quot;Effective Date&quot; at the top of this Privacy
						Policy.</p>
				</div>
				<h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
				<div class='card'>
					<p>If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or the handling of your personal
						information, please contact us at <a href='mailto:support@triplay.ai'>support@triplay.ai</a>.</p>
				</div>
				<p>Your use of the Website signifies your acceptance of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this
					policy, please do not use our Website. Your continued use of the Website following the posting of changes to
					this policy will be deemed as your acceptance of those changes.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
